<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="postbody">The numbers that matter:
<br />

<br />
Fully focus'd and AA'd heal:mana ratio and heal:sec ratios on heals.
<br />

<br />
Fully focus'd and AA'd rune:mana ratio and <span style="font-weight: bold">total rune</span> amounts.
<br />

<br />
This gives us two measures
<br />

<br />
heal:rune efficiency ratio.  This tells us how efficiency has compared.
<br />

<br />
rune-seconds/heal tells us how long we should expect runes to last.  Mob DPS goes up with tank mitigation and cleric healing: rune duration goes down with mob DPS.
<br />

<br />
At L 60, pre-focus in Luclin, the aggregate rune is:
<br />
1050 rune 550 mana or 1.91 rune:mana
<br />
With AAs, ratio can get up to 2.55
<br />

<br />
L 60 pre-focus Luclin heals:
<br />
1600 heal 525 mana or 3.05 heal:mana
<br />
With AAs: (average)
<br />
1920 heal 394 mana or 4.87 heal:mana 307 heal:sec
<br />

<br />
1.91 heal:rune efficiency
<br />
3.42 rune-seconds:heal relative rune duration
<br />

<br />

<br />
L 70 current runes:
<br />
3607 rune 803 mana or 4.49 rune:mana
<br />
heals:
<br />
4150 heal 775 mana 3.75 seconds
<br />
focused:
<br />
6225 heal 503.8 mana 2.51 seconds or 12.36 heal:mana and 1243 heal:second
<br />

<br />
2.75 heal:rune efficiency
<br />
2.90 rune-seconds:heal relative rune duration
<br />

<br />
In other words, total self-rune in OOW is better than total self-rune in Luclin.
<br />

<br />
Of course, total self-rune in Luclin was garbage.  =)  But with arcane rune, enchanter self-rune did get better.
<br />

<br />
(heals 2.5 recast delay included in above heal:second math)
<br />

<br />
Anyone want to run the numbers for Pop era vs current era?</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
</td></tr>
<br />
